cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CL

The paper proposes a deep learning model for flow prediction with features of spatial-temporal. This involves the use of attention mechanisms to capture both spatial and temporal dependencies. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of real-world data, which suggests the possibility of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as potential sub-categories.
